(21, 'TikTok users left petrified by ‘convincing ghost video which shows spirit removing dog’s collar’ | indy100', 'https://www.indy100.com/viral/ghost-video-spirit-removing-dog-collar-tiktok-b1942895', '    newsviralpoliticscelebritiessportscience and techvideoWishlistConversationsLogin Person   TikTok users left petrified by ‘convincing ghost video which shows spirit removing dog’s collar’Breanna Robinson Thursday 21 October 2021 19:52ViralUpvote Upvote TikTok users say they were left petrified after a woman posted one of the most “convincing” ghost videos they’ve ever encountered.\n\nThe woman was rewatching home security footage of her dogs when she believed she spotted a “ghost” intervention. Sharing the clip, she urged people to pay close attention to her black dog.\n\n“Sorry for the obnoxious barking at the beginning. Watch my black dog. [A] ghost takes her collar off in her crate,” she wrote in the video’s caption.\n\nIn the video, you see the two dogs, who are in separate crates barking at each other in what appears to be a living room.RecommendedTikTok has a new Squid Game filter - and it’s even scarier than the robot dollMan receives bizarre text from date’s mum - but it’s weirder than it first seemsMum reveals huge difference in size 14 jeans despite buying from same shop\n\nBoth dogs bark profusely until around the 23-second mark in the video when the pups ceased all noise, standing alert for a moment.\n\nThe black dog, who is in the crate to the right begins to whimper and then suddenly jumps back into a corner of the crate, seemingly trying to avoid something once its collar randomly pops off.\n\nSign up to our new free Indy100 weekly newsletter\n\nIt was at this moment that the owner was certain that a ‘ghost’ was responsible—and others agreed.\n\nSince the video was posted, it accrued over 1.3 million views at the time of writing and over 43,600 comments from people who think it’s a ghost as well.\n\n“They both got super quiet...they felt the energy,” someone wrote.\n\n“I’ve never seen such a convincing ghost video,” another added while a third noted that a seeming entity messing with dogs “doesn’t sit right” with them.\n\nOn the other hand, others believed there were logical explanations as to why the collar magically came off, with some saying that it was “stiff fabric” that caused the collar to unclasp or it simply “came off by accident and the dog got scared.”\n\nNo matter what transpired, it’s safe to say that the case of the fallen collar appeared to be creepy nonetheless.More About: TikTokGhost       back to topUser PoliciesPrivacyCookiesFeedbackAbout indy100ArchiveTrending Elon Musk wants to open a university with a very immature name2021-10-29T11:02:22.000ZAmazon driver fired after video of woman leaving his van goes viral2021-10-31T11:42:15.000ZMelania gave a priceless facial expression after looking at Trump2021-10-31T14:09:07.000ZMan criticised for shaming his wife for bleeding after giving birth2021-10-31T13:28:32.000ZWoman shocked after she found out she was pregnant on the toilet2021-10-30T16:13:20.000ZSister accused of ‘upstaging’ bride after 100-pound weight loss2021-11-01T09:01:29.000ZMAFS Australia’s Jessika Power reveals her hilarious UK bucket list2021-10-29T15:13:44.000ZWhen do the clocks go back and will we lose or gain an hour of sleep?2021-10-30T11:22:32.000ZWoman claims her life is harder because she is ‘attractive’2021-11-01T09:39:36.000ZWoman discovers she’s accidentally been exposing herself to neighbours2021-10-29T09:26:29.000ZBabysitter who called cops on mom questions if she did the right thing2021-10-30T08:09:01.000ZCNN reporter confronts PM over being maskless next to Attenborough2021-11-03T10:06:42.000ZInfluencer sparks outrage posing for photos on Holocaust memorial2021-11-02T08:24:05.000ZCaitlyn Jenner: Dave Chappelle is ‘100% right’ in Netflix row2021-10-28T08:10:36.000ZBoris Johnson at the G20 Summit has sparked Benny Hill comparisons2021-10-31T10:36:20.000ZWhy was there 